    </p>
  </div>

<div class="mx-5 md:mx-20 ">
  
  <h1 class="font-heading text-red text-4xl uppercase mb-5">
    Welcome to Melbourne's <span class="text-nowrap">Bloodiest Evening</span>.
  </h1>

  <div class="flex md:block flex-col-reverse gap-10 my-2">
      <img
        src="./img/R0A4296.jpg"
        width="600"
        height="400"
        class="rounded-2xl md:float-right md:max-w-1/2 md:m-4 float-none"
      />
    
      <div>
        <p>
          <span class="font-bold">Midnight in Melbourne</span> is a casual
          live-action roleplay set in the vampire society of Melbourne,
          illustrating the scenario drawn from Vampire: The Masquerade.
        </p>
        <p>
          We aim to be a beginner-friendly event, with an ongoing interactive
          story. Each of our events is a sequel to the preceding one, but you
          can come without knowing what's happened in previous sessions (but if you're curious, you can read summaries in the "History and Lore" page). 
        </p>
        <p>
          The experience is similar to playing a session of Dungeons & Dragons,
          engaging in improvisational theatre exercises, or participating in a
          murder mystery soiree.
        </p>
      
      <p>No prior experience is needed.</p>
    </div>
  
</div>
</div>



<div class="flex flex-col items-center mx-20">
  <h1 class="font-heading text-red text-4xl uppercase mb-5">The current Clans of Melbourne</h1>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-10 justify-center">
    {% for item in collections.clans %}
    <div
      class="flex flex-col gap-1 items-center cursor-pointer"
      data-modal-target="modal-clan-{{item.page.fileSlug}}"
      data-modal-toggle="modal-clan-{{item.page.fileSlug}}"
    >
      <img src="{{item.data.thumbnailImg}}" class="rounded" />
      {{item.data.title}}
    </div>
    {% else %} Error: No clans! {% endfor %}
  </div>
</div>
<div class="mx-5 md:mx-20">

  <h1 class="font-heading text-red text-4xl uppercase mb-5 mt-20"> What to expect</h1>
  <p>
    On arrival, players are assigned a clan according to vibe and dress code. 
    Confident participants may choose a vampiric ability (Discipline) associated with their clan, which will be provided and explained by their assigned clan Storyteller who will help to guide them through the event and answer any questions. 
    Over the course of the evening, the decisions and actions of players will shape the story of the vampiric underworld of Melbourne. 
  </p>
  <p>
  A standard game involves predominantly roleplay and social machinations, occasionally interrupted by a  <span class="font-bold">Witching Hour</span> during which combat can occur. At the end of the night, 
  players vote for  <span class="font-bold">Hunting Grounds</span> - sections of Melbourne dominated by a particular clan. All clans that have successfully claimed at least one Hunting Ground may continue with their presence
  in Melbourne, while unsuccessful clans are driven out and will be unavailable for play in the following event. 
  <p>
    Each event involves minimal mechanics (see the Resources page), and emphasises cosplay and cocktails. Our events run every three months, on a Sunday closest to the 13th.   
  </p>
</div>
